@startuml Message Passing - Fire-and-Forget vs Request-Reply

title Message Passing: tell() vs ask()

participant Sender as sender
participant "Proc<S,M>" as proc
participant Mailbox as mailbox
participant "Message Loop" as loop
participant Handler as handler

== Fire-and-Forget: tell(msg) ==

sender -> proc: tell(msg)
note right of sender
  Non-blocking
  Returns immediately
end note
proc -> mailbox: offer(msg)
mailbox --> proc: true (enqueued)
proc --> sender: void (fire & forget)

loop -> mailbox: poll()
mailbox --> loop: msg
loop -> handler: apply(state, msg)
handler --> loop: newState

== Request-Reply: ask(msg, timeout) ==

sender -> proc: ask(msg, timeout)
note right of sender
  Returns CompletableFuture<S>
  Blocks on future.get()
end note
proc -> mailbox: offer(msg)
mailbox --> proc: CompletableFuture<S>
proc --> sender: future

sender -> sender: block on future.get()

loop -> mailbox: poll()
mailbox --> loop: msg
loop -> handler: apply(state, msg)
handler --> loop: newState
loop -> proc: future.complete(newState)

proc --> sender: newState (returns from blocking)
note right of sender
  Can timeout if takes too long
  throws TimeoutException
end note
